-- Apple Supplier Flextronics Fires Employee Amid U.S. Insider-Trading Probe
-- B y   A d a m   S a t a r i a n o
-- 2010-12-17T19:09:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/flextronics-fires-employee-shimoon-after-arrest-in-insider-trading-probe.html
Flextronics International Ltd.
employee Walter Shimoon, who was arrested this week as part of a
federal insider-trading investigation, has been fired, the
company said.  “Flextronics has a practice of fully cooperating with
regulatory inquiries and has clear policies prohibiting the
release of confidential information about the company and its
business partners,” Renee Brotherton, a spokeswoman for
Flextronics, said today in a statement. The company supplies
Apple Inc. with cameras and battery chargers for its devices.  To contact the reporter on this story:
